com.gembox.spreadsheet

Class ExcelFillPattern

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gembox.spreadsheet.ExcelFillPattern

  • public final class ExcelFillPattern
extends Object
    Represents cell fill (background) formatting which can be either pattern or gradient.

    Following code demonstrates fill formatting: 

    // 'Fill' formatting group

sheet.getCell("B24").setValue("FillPattern.setPattern(...)");
sheet.getCell("C24").getStyle().getFillPattern().setPattern(FillPatternStyle.THIN_HORIZONTAL_CROSSHATCH, SpreadsheetColor.fromName(ColorName.GREEN), SpreadsheetColor.fromName(ColorName.YELLOW));

sheet.getCell("B25").setValue("FillPattern.setGradient(...)");
sheet.getCell("C25").getStyle().getFillPattern().setGradient(GradientShadingStyle.HORIZONTAL_HIGH, SpreadsheetColor.fromName(ColorName.GREEN), SpreadsheetColor.fromName(ColorName.YELLOW));
    See Also:
    CellStyle.setFillPattern(com.gembox.spreadsheet.ExcelFillPattern)

      • setPatternStyle

        public void setPatternStyle(FillPatternStyle patternStyle)

        Sets the pattern fill style.

        Default value is FillPatternStyle.NONE.

        Currently supported only in XLSX and XLS. For all other formats it defaults to either FillPatternStyle.NONE or FillPatternStyle.SOLID.

        If set value is not FillPatternStyle.NONE, then setPatternForegroundColor(com.gembox.spreadsheet.SpreadsheetColor) and/or setPatternBackgroundColor(com.gembox.spreadsheet.SpreadsheetColor) should also be set.

        Parameters:
        patternStyle - The pattern fill style.

      • setSolid

        public void setSolid(SpreadsheetColor fillColor)

        Sets the solid pattern fill with the specified fill color.

        Sets setPatternStyle(com.gembox.spreadsheet.FillPatternStyle) to FillPatternStyle.SOLID and setPatternForegroundColor(com.gembox.spreadsheet.SpreadsheetColor) to fillColor.

        Parameters:
        fillColor - Foreground color of the solid pattern fill.
